Commentary: Good stop from Zakir Hasan! Top length from Taskin right away as he pitches it up a bit on off, Yashasvi Jaiswal waits well and dabs it with soft hands wide of fourth slip where it is well stopped.
Default_Commentary: 0.1: Taskin Ahmed to Yashasvi Jaiswal, No run.

Commentary: Taskin hammers the ball on his favorite hard length and bowls it wider of the off stump, a bit of seam movement away from the left-hander and Jaiswal leaves it alone.
Default_Commentary: 0.2: Taskin Ahmed to Yashasvi Jaiswal, No run.

Commentary: Beautifully bowled! Hard length again and on a much tighter line around off, a bit of movement away as well, Jaiswal hops back and pushes inside the line. Excellent carry on that one as well.
Default_Commentary: 0.3: Taskin Ahmed to Yashasvi Jaiswal, No run.

Commentary: A loud cheer from the crowd as Jaiswal and India get off the mark! Just full of a good length and a lot straighter, this one nips back into the pads and Jaiswal just tucks it down to fine leg for a single.
Default_Commentary: 0.4: Taskin Ahmed to Yashasvi Jaiswal, 1 run.

Commentary: Shortens the length and bowls it fairly wide outside off, shaping further away, Rohit Sharma watches it well and lets it through.
Default_Commentary: 0.5: Taskin Ahmed to Rohit Sharma, No run.

Commentary: Oh, that shot off the deck! Taskin bangs it in on a hard length again and outside off, gets the ball to move away with some extra bounce. Rohit Sharma has a waft at it but the ball flies past the outside edge. A controlled first over from Taskin, India are 1/0.
Default_Commentary: 0.6: Taskin Ahmed to Rohit Sharma, No run.

Commentary: A bit too straight to begin with! Fuller in length on middle and leg, sliding on, Yashasvi Jaiswal nudges it off the inner half of the blade down to fine leg and picks up a single.
Default_Commentary: 1.1: Hasan Mahmud to Yashasvi Jaiswal, 1 run.

Commentary: Pitched up wide of the off stump and swinging away from the right-hander, left alone by Sharma.
Default_Commentary: 1.2: Hasan Mahmud to Rohit Sharma, No run.

Commentary: Angles the ball in from wide of the off stump and gets it to gently shape away, Rohit Sharma presses halfway forward before leaving it alone.
Default_Commentary: 1.3: Hasan Mahmud to Rohit Sharma, No run.

Commentary: Full again, around the fifth stump line and this one swings back in a touch, a well-watched leave again from Sharma.
Default_Commentary: 1.4: Hasan Mahmud to Rohit Sharma, No run.

Commentary: Too wide to make the batter play at it. Full length again but Mahmud spills the ball well wide of the off stump and Rohit Sharma lets it through to the keeper yet again.
Default_Commentary: 1.5: Hasan Mahmud to Rohit Sharma, No run.

Commentary: Five leaves in a row and almost each of those leaves was an easy one as well. Nagging length again but Mahmud seems to have his line wrong as this is bowled fairly wide outside off as well.
Default_Commentary: 1.6: Hasan Mahmud to Rohit Sharma, No run.

Commentary: Caulker of a delivery from Taskin! Good length at 136.6 kph and on off stump, the ball is angled in but leaves the left-hander sharply after pitching. Yashasvi Jaiswal looks to block but the ball zips past the outside edge with good carry again.
Default_Commentary: 2.1: Taskin Ahmed to Yashasvi Jaiswal, No run.

Commentary: Loses some control now does Taskin and bowls a fullish delivery down the leg side, it swings further down and Litton Das cannot collect it cleanly. The batters get a bye.
Default_Commentary: 2.2: Taskin Ahmed to Yashasvi Jaiswal, Bye.

Commentary: On a hard length and on the fifth stump line, this one pitches and shapes away quite a fair bit as Rohit Sharma presses back and leaves it alone.
Default_Commentary: 2.3: Taskin Ahmed to Rohit Sharma, No run.

Commentary: Much fuller this time, wanting the batter to drive at it but the line is a bit too wide of the off stump and Rohit presses forward before making yet another leave.
Default_Commentary: 2.4: Taskin Ahmed to Rohit Sharma, No run.

Commentary: The big in-dipper now that takes Rohit Sharma completely by surprise. Taskin goes wide on the crease and hammers it on a hard length outside off, the ball lands and jags back in a mile. Sharma looks to defend but is beaten on the inside edge and gets hit high on the thigh pad.
Default_Commentary: 2.5: Taskin Ahmed to Rohit Sharma, No run.

Commentary: Sharma is off the mark! Full and around off, looking for the away-swinger, Rohit Sharma dabs it away onto the off side and scampers across for a quick single.
Default_Commentary: 2.6: Taskin Ahmed to Rohit Sharma, 1 run.

Commentary: Perfect length on off and middle, nipping back in a touch, Sharma plays it with soft hands and flicks it away to mid-wicket.
Default_Commentary: 3.1: Hasan Mahmud to Rohit Sharma, No run.

Commentary: Oh, that is a good ball! Huge shouts for LBW but the umpire remains unmoved. Najmul Hossain Shanto has a word with his players and opts for the review. Hasan Mahmud pitches the ball up around off stump and gets it to nip back in sharply off the deck. Rohit Sharma looks to get forward and play it with a straight bat but is beaten past the inside edge and gets pinged on the back leg. Nothing on UltraEdge and Ball Tracking shows the wickets as the umpire's call and Sharma survives. Bangladesh does not lose a review, but this is a decent start for the visitors.
Default_Commentary: 3.2: Hasan Mahmud to Rohit Sharma, No run.

Commentary: Pitched up around the fifth stump line and this one goes straight on, Sharma plants his front leg across and blocks it towards cover-point.
Default_Commentary: 3.3: Hasan Mahmud to Rohit Sharma, No run.

Commentary: BEATEN! Hasan Mahmud is bowling brilliantly to the right-hander. That in-between length, drawing the batter halfway forward and as Sharma looks to present the full face of the bat at it, the ball deviates away and beats the outside edge by a whisker.
Default_Commentary: 3.4: Hasan Mahmud to Rohit Sharma, No run.

Commentary: Bowls this one a bit wider and it is the one that angles back in a long way, Rohit Sharma plays it late and right in front of the stumps before blocking it towards mid on.
Default_Commentary: 3.5: Hasan Mahmud to Rohit Sharma, No run.

Commentary: FOUR! Uppish but in the gap and that will be the first boundary of the Test match. Floated up full and outside off, Rohit Sharma is able to get forward and drive through the line and through the big gap between covers and point for a boundary.
Default_Commentary: 3.6: Hasan Mahmud to Rohit Sharma, Four!

Commentary: More than half a shout for caught behind but it is turned down. Banged in on a hard length and around leg, Yashasvi Jaiswal looks to work it off the hips but the ball swings in a bit and just goes past the edge.
Default_Commentary: 4.1: Taskin Ahmed to Yashasvi Jaiswal, No run.

Commentary: FOUR! Top shot from Jaiswal! Too full and straight, all the swing is negated by the length and Jaiswal just clears the front leg before whipping it across through mid-wicket for a boundary.
Default_Commentary: 4.2: Taskin Ahmed to Yashasvi Jaiswal, Four!

Commentary: Back of a length this time and around off, angling further away, Jaiswal shoulders arms at it.
Default_Commentary: 4.3: Taskin Ahmed to Yashasvi Jaiswal, No run.

Commentary: Pitched up down the leg side and the ball just flies off the deck, no chance of Jaiswal getting a bat on it and its a good take behind the stumps from Litton Das.
Default_Commentary: 4.4: Taskin Ahmed to Yashasvi Jaiswal, No run.

Commentary: Hard length over middle and leg, Yashasvi Jaiswal waits back and works it away with soft hands through backward square leg and picks up a single.
Default_Commentary: 4.5: Taskin Ahmed to Yashasvi Jaiswal, 1 run.

Commentary: Drop and run! Hits the deck hard, bowling it with an upright seam over off, Rohit Sharma hops and blocks it to the off side before getting across quickly for the single.
Default_Commentary: 4.6: Taskin Ahmed to Rohit Sharma, 1 run.

Commentary: OUT! EDGED AND GONE! The writing was on the wall with that one and Hasan Mahmud does get rid of the Indian skipper with a lovely delivery. Immaculate length, neither full nor short and on off stump, this one angles in but leaves the right-hander after pitching. Rohit Sharma stays put and looks to block with soft hands but the outside edge is found and Najmul Hossain Shanto takes a good low catch at second slip. India 14/1 as Sharma goes for 6 (19).
Default_Commentary: 5.1: Hasan Mahmud to Rohit Sharma, OUT! c Najmul Hossain Shanto b Hasan Mahmud.
Howout: c Najmul Hossain Shanto b Hasan Mahmud

Commentary: Lovely bowling this from Hasan Mahmud and consistent as well. Nagging length on the fourth stump line, this one holds its line, Shubman Gill looks to block off the front foot but the ball whizzes past the outside edge.
Default_Commentary: 5.2: Hasan Mahmud to Shubman Gill, No run.

Commentary: There's that change up again that nips back in. Quite full and around off, angling back in sharply, Gill manages to take the front leg out and blocks it off.
Default_Commentary: 5.3: Hasan Mahmud to Shubman Gill, No run.

Commentary: Good length, wide of the off stump and angling further away, left alone by Gill.
Default_Commentary: 5.4: Hasan Mahmud to Shubman Gill, No run.

Commentary: On a good length again and wide of the off stump, swinging away with some extra bounce, Gill doesn't play at it.
Default_Commentary: 5.5: Hasan Mahmud to Shubman Gill, No run.

Commentary: Full and wide outside off, not much movement on this one but another easy leave for Shubman Gill to make. End of a wicket-maiden from Hasan Mahmud.
Default_Commentary: 5.6: Hasan Mahmud to Shubman Gill, No run.

Commentary: Back of a length over middle, banged in, Jaiswal hops back to defend.
Default_Commentary: 6.1: Taskin Ahmed to Yashasvi Jaiswal, No run.

Commentary: Short of a length again, this time on the hips, Jaiswal tucks it away neatly and gets it well wide of fine leg for a couple of runs.
Default_Commentary: 6.2: Taskin Ahmed to Yashasvi Jaiswal, 2 runs.

Commentary: Well left! Better length from Taskin as he pitches it up a bit on off and gets the ball to shoot off the deck, Jaiswal does well to press back and lift his arms and let it through to the keeper.
Default_Commentary: 6.3: Taskin Ahmed to Yashasvi Jaiswal, No run.

Commentary: FOUR! That was exquisite from Jaiswal! Overpitched now and outside off, Jaiswal leans into the shot and drives it firmly through covers, even holding the pose to find the fence.
Default_Commentary: 6.4: Taskin Ahmed to Yashasvi Jaiswal, Four!

Commentary: Just short of a length again and in and around the off stump line, Jaiswal shoulders arms at it.
Default_Commentary: 6.5: Taskin Ahmed to Yashasvi Jaiswal, No run.

Commentary: FOUR! Hammered away! Taskin changes the angle of attack by coming around the stumps and serves it right in the slot on off, Yashasvi Jaiswal gets his body weight forward and pings the on drive through the vacant mid on region for another boundary.
Default_Commentary: 6.6: Taskin Ahmed to Yashasvi Jaiswal, Four!

Commentary: FOUR BYES! A surprise loosener from Hasan Mahmud and no chance for Litton Das to cut that one off. Slightly full and angled down leg, this one just keeps on going and rolls away to the fine leg fence for four bonus runs.
Default_Commentary: 7.1: Hasan Mahmud to Shubman Gill, 4 Byes.

Commentary: A half-hearted appeal for LBW but it is turned down. The in-between length on off, the ball angles back in and Shubman Gill plays all around the delivery and gets hit on pads. No review taken and that looked pretty high as well.
Default_Commentary: 7.2: Hasan Mahmud to Shubman Gill, No run.

Commentary: OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Shubman Gill will be kicking himself and that is a soft dismissal. Hasan Mahmud looks for the delivery that angles back in as he knows Gill has a weakness with that but gets the line wrong and spills it down leg. Gill looks to flick and is drawn well forward and somehow manages to edge it down to the keeper. Litton Das moves swiftly to his left and takes the catch. Gill departs for a duck and India in early trouble at 28/2!
Default_Commentary: 7.3: Hasan Mahmud to Shubman Gill, OUT! c Litton Das b Hasan Mahmud.
Howout: c Litton Das b Hasan Mahmud

Commentary: On a hard length and in the channel around off, this one nips back in a touch as Virat Kohli leaves it alone.
Default_Commentary: 7.4: Hasan Mahmud to Virat Kohli, No run.

Commentary: Full and straight, looking to slide one through the gate but Kohli is able to play that signature wristy flick and gets it down to deep square leg for a single.
Default_Commentary: 7.5: Hasan Mahmud to Virat Kohli, 1 run.

Commentary: Pitched up in and around the off stump line, gently swinging in a bit as Jaiswal makes a watchful leave.
Default_Commentary: 7.6: Hasan Mahmud to Yashasvi Jaiswal, No run.

Commentary: Back of a length and around off, Virat Kohli presses back and plays it late with an angled bat and dabs it down past the gully fielder for a couple of runs.
Default_Commentary: 8.1: Taskin Ahmed to Virat Kohli, 2 runs.

Commentary: Nicely timed and good running as well. Slightly pitched up around middle, sliding right on, Kohli gets forward and just pushes the ball with fine timing through the mid-wicket region and picks up three runs as Hasan Mahmud chases it down.
Default_Commentary: 8.2: Taskin Ahmed to Virat Kohli, 3 runs.

Commentary: Back of a length and in the channel around off, Jaiswal gets on his toes and nudges it down behind point.
Default_Commentary: 8.3: Taskin Ahmed to Yashasvi Jaiswal, No run.

Commentary: Taskin grunts in as he serves a bumper at 133 kph and right over middle and leg, Jaiswal ducks under it fairly comfortably.
Default_Commentary: 8.4: Taskin Ahmed to Yashasvi Jaiswal, No run.

Commentary: On a good length now and around middle and leg, Jaiswal gets a bit forward and defends it with a straight bat.
Default_Commentary: 8.5: Taskin Ahmed to Yashasvi Jaiswal, No run.

Commentary: Good length again, this time around off and angling away, left alone by Jaiswal.
Default_Commentary: 8.6: Taskin Ahmed to Yashasvi Jaiswal, No run.

Commentary: Pitched up wide of the off stump, looking to angle it back in, Kohli gets well forward and blocks it on the full towards covers.
Default_Commentary: 9.1: Hasan Mahmud to Virat Kohli, No run.

Commentary: OUT! EDGED AND GONE! Hasan Mahmud will be on cloud nine as he gets a third wicket and the Indian right-handers just can't seem to play against him at the moment. Lovely length from Mahmud but the line is a bit wide of the off stump. It still draws the batter forward and Virat Kohli looks to drive with hard hands and that slight away movement means a faint outside edge is found. The ball nestles into the gloves of Litton Das behind the stumps and India in a spot of real bother now at 34/3 inside the first 10 overs.
Default_Commentary: 9.2: Hasan Mahmud to Virat Kohli, OUT! c Litton Das b Hasan Mahmud.
Howout: c Litton Das b Hasan Mahmud

Commentary: Slightly fuller and in the channel outside off, this one zips off the deck as Rishabh Pant leaves it alone.
Default_Commentary: 9.3: Hasan Mahmud to Rishabh Pant, No run.

Commentary: Mahmud bends his back a bit more and bangs this one in short and outside off, the ball wobbles away as well and Pant makes a good leave.
Default_Commentary: 9.4: Hasan Mahmud to Rishabh Pant, No run.

Commentary: That three-quarter length, on off and middle and angling back in, Rishabh Pant looks to get forward and block but gets an inside edge onto the pad.
Default_Commentary: 9.5: Hasan Mahmud to Rishabh Pant, No run.

Commentary: Another wicket-maiden for Hasan Mahmud and Bangladesh are on top of proceedings at the moment. Pitched up around the fourth stump line, Pant stays low and eases it towards point looking for a single but is sent back.
Default_Commentary: 9.6: Hasan Mahmud to Rishabh Pant, No run.

Commentary: Rana steams in from over the wicket and clocks 146 kph right away. This is bowled short and right at the batter, Jaiswal hops back and does well to keep it down.
Default_Commentary: 10.1: Nahid Rana to Yashasvi Jaiswal, No run.

Commentary: Oh, that is spicy! Almost 142 clicks and banged in short over middle, the line is perfect and Rana gets that sharp bounce as well. Jaiswal bends his back and sways away from the line of the ball.
Default_Commentary: 10.2: Nahid Rana to Yashasvi Jaiswal, No run.

Commentary: This is really aggressive bowling from Nahid Rana first up. Not all that quick at 136.6 kph but the line and length is perfect. Banged in right around the helmet and shooting off the deck, Jaiswal does well again to somehow duck under that one.
Default_Commentary: 10.3: Nahid Rana to Yashasvi Jaiswal, No run.

Commentary: No ball! Rana brings out the slower delivery now but he has overstepped here. On a good length and outside off, Jaiswal waits well and taps it away towards cover.
Default_Commentary: 10.4: Nahid Rana to Yashasvi Jaiswal, No ball!

Commentary: Hard length around off stump, Jaiswal presses back and punches it through the gap at covers for a run.
Default_Commentary: 10.4: Nahid Rana to Yashasvi Jaiswal, 1 run.

Commentary: Classic Pant, no idea what kind of shot that was. Short of a length and around off stump, Rishabh Pant seems off balanced and just looks to have a swipe across the line but misses.
Default_Commentary: 10.5: Nahid Rana to Rishabh Pant, No run.

Commentary: Back of a length and outside off stump, a much more classical leave by Pant this time.
Default_Commentary: 10.6: Nahid Rana to Rishabh Pant, No run.

Commentary: Hasan Mahmud bowls it across off, it pitches around off and nips away gently, Yashasvi Jaiswal pushes forward but aborts from the block.
Default_Commentary: 11.1: Hasan Mahmud to Yashasvi Jaiswal, No run.

Commentary: At 130.2 kph, full and around off, Yashasvi Jaiswal pushes it off the inner half of the willow towards wide of mid on and fetches a quick single.
Default_Commentary: 11.2: Hasan Mahmud to Yashasvi Jaiswal, 1 run.

Commentary: Good shot, and good running as well! Short of a good length, around middle and leg, Rishabh Pant prods forward and flicks it nonchalantly through mid-wicket. However, the ball loses its steam as it nears the boundary ropes and Nahid Rana chases it from mid on and slips a bit with the momentum which allows the batters to hurry for the third run.
Default_Commentary: 11.3: Hasan Mahmud to Rishabh Pant, 3 runs.

Commentary: Wide outside off on a length, left alone.
Default_Commentary: 11.4: Hasan Mahmud to Yashasvi Jaiswal, No run.

Commentary: A huge appeal for LBW but the umpire says 'No'! Bangladesh do not opt for a review this time. This is a good length ball, angling away on off, Yashasvi Jaiswal wants to leave but the ball pings his pads instead. Probably going outside off.
Default_Commentary: 11.5: Hasan Mahmud to Yashasvi Jaiswal, No run.

Commentary: Length, outside off, Jaiswal makes a watchful leave.
Default_Commentary: 11.6: Hasan Mahmud to Yashasvi Jaiswal, No run.

Commentary: FOUR! Now, that's a good shot from Pant! Nahid Rana bangs it into the surface and clocks 140.3 kph, but the line is wide outside off on a hard length, Rishabh Pant gets the desired bounce and width, climbs on the bounce and cuts it behind square with firm hands for a boundary at deep backward point.
Default_Commentary: 12.1: Nahid Rana to Rishabh Pant, Four!

Commentary: Risky running, to say the least! That was touch and go had it been a direct hit. Nahid Rana goes full and around off, Rishabh Pant taps it with soft hands next to the strip and sets off for a single. Yashasvi Jaiswal though had to put the afterburners to get home safely at the striker's end. Zakir Hasan from the slips runs forward and slides to pick and throw but has a shy at the batter's end and he crashes into the sticks instead. India get a risky single.
Default_Commentary: 12.2: Nahid Rana to Rishabh Pant, 1 run.

Commentary: Back of a length on the middle stump. Jaiswal gets onto the back foot and blocks it to the left of the bowler.
Default_Commentary: 12.3: Nahid Rana to Yashasvi Jaiswal, No run.

Commentary: Short of a length on the off stump. Jaiswal hops back and pushes it to cover for a single.
Default_Commentary: 12.4: Nahid Rana to Yashasvi Jaiswal, 1 run.

Commentary: A low full toss just outside the off stump. Pant pushes it out off the toe end to mid off.
Default_Commentary: 12.5: Nahid Rana to Rishabh Pant, No run.

Commentary: Hard length now, on the leg stump line, Rishabh Pant stays on the back foot and taps it with soft hands to square leg. End of another chaotic over.
Default_Commentary: 12.6: Nahid Rana to Rishabh Pant, No run.

Commentary: Hasan in his extended spell, comes from around the pegs, hurls it full and angles it around off, Yashasvi Jaiswal has a feel for it initially but gets beaten on the front foot.
Default_Commentary: 13.1: Hasan Mahmud to Yashasvi Jaiswal, No run.

Commentary: Full and shaping away a touch from outside off, Yashasvi Jaiswal weighs forward and lifts his bat in the air to make the leave.
Default_Commentary: 13.2: Hasan Mahmud to Yashasvi Jaiswal, No run.

Commentary: Too full and outside off, jagging back a bit, and probing Jaiswal to have a poke at it, but Jaiswal shows no interest and lets it pass.
Default_Commentary: 13.3: Hasan Mahmud to Yashasvi Jaiswal, No run.

Commentary: FOUR! Great shot that! An inswinger from Hasan Mahmud, angling on the off stump line and finishing at the middle stump, Yashasvi Jaiswal walks a couple of steps ahead to negate the swing, meets the ball underneath his eyes, middles it from the bat, and flicks it with the angled bat through the vacant mid-wicket region for a classic boundary. 50 up for India.
Default_Commentary: 13.4: Hasan Mahmud to Yashasvi Jaiswal, Four!

Commentary: This one stays straight, full and outside off, Yashasvi Jaiswal lets it go alone.
Default_Commentary: 13.5: Hasan Mahmud to Yashasvi Jaiswal, No run.

Commentary: Bangs it on a hard length, around off, it bounces a bit more off the deck and Yashasvi Jaiswal is forced to make a quick leave.
Default_Commentary: 13.6: Hasan Mahmud to Yashasvi Jaiswal, No run.

Commentary: Rana continues from over the stumps, clocks 144.3 kph and lands it full and angles across off, Rishabh Pant lets it go through alone.
Default_Commentary: 14.1: Nahid Rana to Rishabh Pant, No run.

Commentary: Bowls his natural length now. Back of a length, on middle and off, at 138.8 kph, Rishabh Pant stays upright and dabs it to the pitch.
Default_Commentary: 14.2: Nahid Rana to Rishabh Pant, No run.

Commentary: FOUR! Nicely driven! Nahid Rana bowls it fuller now, and almost a half volley on off, Rishabh Pant taps his front leg ahead to weigh forward and drives it firmly through the cover-point region for a boundary. The fielder from deep backward point runs to his left to intercept the ball but it wins the race.
Default_Commentary: 14.3: Nahid Rana to Rishabh Pant, Four!

Commentary: The fielder at deep point is much squarer now. Full and on a same line, Rishabh Pant drives it through the point region for a single.
Default_Commentary: 14.4: Nahid Rana to Rishabh Pant, 1 run.

Commentary: Full in length, in front of the pegs, Yashasvi Jaiswal flicks it with his wrists through mid-wicket and scampers back for the second, the ball loses its gas on the way to the boundary and Hasan Mahmud mops it up with a slide, throws back to the bowler's end. The batters think for the third but a good throw from Hasan forces them to settle for two.
Default_Commentary: 14.5: Nahid Rana to Yashasvi Jaiswal, 2 runs.

Commentary: Good delivery! Back of a length, nipping slightly into the batter, over the top of off, Yashasvi Jaiswal gets on his toes to punch it but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Default_Commentary: 14.6: Nahid Rana to Yashasvi Jaiswal, No run.

Commentary: Taskin with four slips, spills it down leg. Rishabh Pant lets it pass.
Default_Commentary: 15.1: Taskin Ahmed to Rishabh Pant, No run.

Commentary: Good length that comes back into the middle stump. Pant does well to take his bottom hand off the bat and turn it into the leg side for a quick single.
Default_Commentary: 15.2: Taskin Ahmed to Rishabh Pant, 1 run.

Commentary: There seems to be a lot of enthusiasm in the middle. A bit of yes and no from the batters but they eventually get one in the end. Hard-length delivery on off, Yashasvi Jaiswal dabs it to point and denies for a single. Mominul Haque picks and throws towards the bowler's end and the overthrow with no proper backup allows them to cross for a single. Litton Das is visibly not happy with it as he reckons Pant was in the way of the throw at the non-striker's end and has a word with Pant about the same.
Default_Commentary: 15.3: Taskin Ahmed to Yashasvi Jaiswal, 1 run.

Commentary: Length ball slanting across and outside off. Pant tries to poke at it and gets beaten on the outside edge.
Default_Commentary: 15.4: Taskin Ahmed to Rishabh Pant, No run.

Commentary: Better length, full and at off, Rishabh Pant taps his front leg ahead and eases it to point with soft hands.
Default_Commentary: 15.5: Taskin Ahmed to Rishabh Pant, No run.

Commentary: Full, attacking the middle stump line, Rishabh Pant gets behind the line of the ball and responds with a solid front foot defence to end the over.
Default_Commentary: 15.6: Taskin Ahmed to Rishabh Pant, No run.

Commentary: Short in length, outside off, Yashasvi Jaiswal gets on his toes and cuts it a bit uppishly and through point for a single.
Default_Commentary: 16.1: Nahid Rana to Yashasvi Jaiswal, 1 run.

Commentary: Too full and angling on off, Rishabh Pant presents a straight bat front foot defence.
Default_Commentary: 16.2: Nahid Rana to Rishabh Pant, No run.

Commentary: Almost a yorker at off but Rishabh Pant does well to squeeze it out with a wristy flick to wide mid on.
Default_Commentary: 16.3: Nahid Rana to Rishabh Pant, No run.

Commentary: FOUR! Pulled away in disdain! Nahid Rana bangs it short and angles on off, Rishabh Pant picks the length early, readies himself with a stable base, swivels and pulls it nicely through square leg for a boundary.
Default_Commentary: 16.4: Nahid Rana to Rishabh Pant, Four!

Commentary: Full and on the fourth stump line, Rishabh Pant crouches a bit and drives it through point for a single.
Default_Commentary: 16.5: Nahid Rana to Rishabh Pant, 1 run.

Commentary: Fired in at 142.9 kph, full, straight and on the middle stump, Yashasvi Jaiswal with a low bat lift, brings the bat straight and pushes it to mid on.
Default_Commentary: 16.6: Nahid Rana to Yashasvi Jaiswal, No run.

Commentary: Outside off, full in length, Rishabh Pant prods ahead and drives it towards deep covers. The timing is not that good which means the ball loses its steam and almost dies in front of deep cover. Two taken though. The outfield is still a bit damp due to the overcast conditions.
Default_Commentary: 17.1: Taskin Ahmed to Rishabh Pant, 2 runs.

Commentary: Fuller in length, on the stumps, Rishabh Pant flicks it to mid on.
Default_Commentary: 17.2: Taskin Ahmed to Rishabh Pant, No run.

Commentary: Everything happening here! Drama! Also, an appeal for LBW, but the umpire says 'No'. Hasan bowls a well-directed yorker on the stumps, Jasprit Bumrah bends to negotiate the yorker and tries to dig it out to the leg side. He does bring his bat down in time but the ball passes closely to the bat and pings his front pad. The ball then rolls towards behind square on the off side. Meanwhile, the fielder there at the off side picks and throws at the non-striker's end but has a huge shy at it and with no proper backup it results in an overthrow, the ball runs towards the deep mid-wicket fence where the fielder from deep square leg just about manages to pull the ball back with a slide. Now, the question is whether he has nicked the ball before the pad. UltraEdge shows a clear deflection off the bat. Not Out it is and the batters take two in the meantime.

FINALLY, A FIVE-WICKET HAUL FOR HASAN MAHMUD AS HE WRAPS THE INDIAN INNINGS WITH A HUGE ACHIEVEMENT! Good length ball around the off stump and it deviates away from the batter after pitching. Bumrah is rooted in the crease and approaches it tentatively getting in an awkward position, plays it away from his body and with an angled bat and gets the outside edge that flies straight into the hands of Zakir Hasan stationed at third slip. Hasan Mahmud becomes the first Bangladeshi pacer to achieve a five-wicket haul on Indian soil, and a very well-deserved one.
Default_Commentary: 91.2: Hasan Mahmud to Jasprit Bumrah, OUT! c Zakir Hasan b Hasan Mahmud.

Commentary: A huge shout for LBW and the Indians almost started celebrating but it is turned down. Mohammed Siraj with a slingy delivery, a tad full and on leg stump, swinging back in. Siraj feels they should take the review but skipper Rohit Sharma feels that might be swinging down leg and they refrain from the review. Uh, oh! The replays later show that if India had reviewed it, it would have been out as the ball was clipping the top of the leg stump on the projection on the Ball Tracker. An opportunity missed and Siraj won't be a happy chap.

Commentary: OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! A huge appeal for caught behind and the on-field umpires discuss for a few seconds and eventually send it upstairs to check for a fair catch. Jadeja quickens the pace and lands it flat and full in the line of the stumps, Shakib Al Hasan sits down on his knee for a reverse sweep but is a bit late on the shot due to that excessive pace from Jadeja. Ends up inside edging it and now the question remains whether the ball has lobbed up straight off his boots or has bounced on the ground. Rishabh Pant meanwhile is very quick to react, moves forward and pouches the ball safely at short leg. The replays eventually come up and affirm that the ball has indeed deflected off Shakib's boot and not the ground. It is deemed as Out and Shakib Al Hasan too, walks back after an unnecessary shot. Bangladesh in all sorts of trouble now with 7 men down.

Commentary: OUT! TAKEN IN THE SLIPS! Bumrah came back for the last burst before the Tea break and delivered magnificently. Commentary: OUT! LBW! A huge, huge shout and eventually, the finger goes up. A wicket against the run of play and Virat Kohli has a chat with Shubman Gill before walking back to the hut. Cleverly bowled by Mehidy Hasan as he darts this one in full and quick around off, Kohli looks to get a stride across and play across the line but ends up playing all around it. The ball pings him in front of off stump and the finger is raised. The only question was of the impact which seems to be in line and Kohli throws away a decent start as he departs for 17 (37). India are now 67/3 with a lead of 294 runs. But surprisingly, the replay later on shows that there was indeed a spike when the ball passed close to the bat. Although, it is not yet sure whether the spike was off the bat in contact with the ground or with the ball. The only person who would've known about the nick was Virat Kohli but he didn't opt for a review. A huge moment in the game, and everyone in the dugout is in a state of shock including Gill on the crease after seeing it on the giant screen.
Default_Commentary: 19.2: Mehidy Hasan to Virat Kohli, OUT! lbw b Mehidy Hasan.

Commentary: OUT! EDGED AND TAKEN! WOW, WHAT A CATCH FROM JAISWAL! He has taken an absolute screamer and finally, India get the first breakthrough. A hard-earned one but Bumrah does the trick. Jasprit Bumrah spears it on the back of a length, and keeps the line outside the off side, it gets a bit of an extra bounce and skids on quickly after pitching. Zakir Hasan gets hurried on the shot and the ball gets heavier on him as well. As a result, he doesn't move his feet and hangs his bat away from his body, and a healthy outside edge is found. The ball carries flat and low in the air towards the right of gully where Yashasvi Jaiswal quickly reacts to it, dives to his wrong side to his right and plucks it out of thin air. And suddenly, the crowd has found its voice in Chennai.

Commentary: OUT! CAUGHT! Catch it is the call! Did that carry? It certainly has and Shadman Islam has to depart now! Ashwin gets his first wicket and Bangladesh have lost both their openers now within the span of half an hour or so. Ashwin bowls it flat and quick on a length, in front of the pegs, Shadman Islam gets across a tad and lazily tries to nudge it away to the leg side, but in this process, he airs it flat and towards Shubman Gill stationed at short mid-wicket. Gill reacts alertly and moves his body low and to the right, and takes a very sharp catch, just inches above the ground. He falls over but manages well to sustain the ball in his hand. A soft dismissal for Shadman Islam as he departs on 35. Also, this is Ravichandran Ashwin's first wicket in this Test.

Commentary: OUT! TAKEN! Ravichandran Ashwin comes into the attack and gets the breakthrough right away, his fourth of this innings as well. Commentary: OUT! CAUGHT! A complete lapse in concentration from Mehidy Hasan and its that man again, Ravichandran Ashwin with another five-fer that too in front of the home crowd and his family as well. A 37th five-wicket haul in Test matches for Ashwin, equalling the late and great Shane Warne as well, just behind Muralitharan's 67 five-wicket haul, a staggering feat indeed. Ashwin drags the length back and flights the ball up on middle and leg, Mehidy skips down the track but doesn't quite get to the pitch of the ball and yet he tries to force the lofted shot. The ball goes high and down to long on where Ravindra Jadeja is stationed and he takes a simple catch. Bangladesh going down in a hurry now.

Commentary: OUT! IN THE AIR AND TAKEN! Jadeja gets his second and Shanto's brilliant innings come to an end. Bangladesh lose their 8th and the most important wicket and now India can sense a win! Jadeja sticks to dart the ball in quick, and just throws it wider outside off, on a shade fuller length, Shanto swings hard at it and looks to lift it over covers but the ball skids through and comes quickly to the bat.
